Package: mass-storage-gadget
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Tom Dewey <tom.dewey@raspberrypi.com>
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: USB mass storage gadget configuration
 Configures the Raspberry Pi as a USB mass storage gadget, exposing
 attached storage devices (eMMC, NVMe, SD, USB) to a connected host
 machine. Also provides a USB serial console via ACM. Useful for
 flashing or imaging devices over USB.
